  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0baa \u0ba8\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Overburdening the people for profit is unacceptable - Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Fuel prices are contradictory. Sri Lanka Public Utility Commission Chairman Janaka Ratnayake said that as a citizen of the country, I have decided to file a complaint with the Human Rights Commission as it is unacceptable to impose a heavy burden on the people for the purpose of profit.",
        "He mentioned the above while attending a press conference held on Thursday 07th at the office of Sri Lanka Public Utility Commission.",
        "The problem is that the fuel prices have been increased in the last one and a half months.",
        "We have paid more attention to the increase in fuel prices because the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka has the power to make decisions about the country's electricity infrastructure.",
        "It has been observed that fuel prices have been improperly increased in the last one and a half months after a complete review of the data related to the fuel imported by Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation and Lanka IOC for the last two months.",
        "Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation spends 298 rupees including customs duty on one liter of 92 octane petrol import and sells one liter of petrol at 470 rupees. On the other hand, the total cost of importing one liter of 95 octane petrol is 303 rupees and its price is 550 rupees.",
        "The import cost of Odo diesel is Rs 112 and the selling price is Rs 460, while the cost of super diesel is Rs 115 before tax and the selling price is Rs 520 before tax.",
        "The statement by the Power Minister that Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation spends Rs 471 per liter of kerosene import is baseless. Only 252 rupees are spent on importing a liter of kerosene.",
        "The Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation supplies the electricity board with 419 rupees per liter of bearish oil but imports 175 rupees per liter of bearish oil.",
        "Fuel price hikes are seen as unfair. Burdens are put on the people for corporate profiteering. It is not acceptable to mention that the Sri Lankan Petroleum Corporation is going bankrupt.",
        "As a citizen of the country, I have decided to file a complaint with the Human Rights Commission regarding the controversial nature of fuel price hike.",
        "He said that I have presented many issues in the Cobb committee. He said that the politicians who criticize specific issues related to the increase in fuel prices can understand that there is ambiguity in this matter."
      ],
